---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <p class="mt-4 lg:mt-0">
    Based in Manila, I love building things that actually make a
    difference from scalable backend systems to creative side projects. I'm
    also an open-source contributor who enjoys sharing what I learn and
    collaborating with the developer community.
  </p>
  <p class="my-4">
    I started coding at 15, writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript on my phone. That
    early curiosity pushed me beyond the web and into low-level projects like
    building compilers and creating my own programming language,{" "}
    <a
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
      href="https://github.com/decimozs/hiraya"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      @Hiraya
    </a>
    . Along the way, I discovered my love for backend engineering and for
    building systems that solve real-world problems.
  </p>
  <p class="my-4">
    I subscribe to a minimalist, functional approach to engineering. When
    creating a product, I prioritize simplicity and maintainability. I believe
    that as systems grow more complex, the architecture must remain lean to
    ensure security, governance, and horizontal scalability.
  </p>
  <p class="my-4">
  Deeply curious, I’m driven by a curiosity for how the world’s most effective engineers solve complex problems. I regularly dive into deep-tech insights and industry newsletters, with {" "} 
  <a href="https://www.pragmaticengineer.com/"
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >@The Pragmatic Engineer</a> 
  {" "} being a cornerstone of my technical diet. This habit of studying production-grade systems informs my minimalist, functional philosophy: as systems grow, architecture must remain lean. By applying these high-leverage principles, I ensure that the autonomous agents and distributed workflows I develop are engineered for horizontal scalability, security, and real-world impact.
  </p>
  <p>
    Right now, I balance my time between working as a remote Backend Engineer
    and serving as an AI Engineer Intern, where I continue to explore the
    latest advancements in LLM architectures. Outside of my technical workflow,
    I am a dedicated runner, currently training for an upcoming marathon.
  </p>
  <p class="my-4">
    To learn more about my background and professional experience, you can view
    my{" "}
    <a
      href="/resume.pdf"
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      id="resume-link"
    >
      resume
    </a>
    . Additionally, to see my work in action, feel free to browse my{" "}
    <a
      href="/works"
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
    >
      works
    </a>
    , explore my contributions on{" "}
    <a
      href="https://github.com/decimozs"
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      id="github-profile-link"
    >
      @github.com/decimozs
    </a>
    , or connect with me on{" "}
    <a
      href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/decimomartin/"
      class="italic text-muted-foreground hover:text-black underline-animate"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      id="linkedin-profile-link"
    >
      @linkedin.com/in/decimomartin
    </a>
    .
  </p>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
  document.getElementById('resume-link')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    window.posthog?.capture('resume_clicked', { source: 'about' });
  });
  document.getElementById('github-profile-link')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    window.posthog?.capture('github_profile_clicked', { source: 'about' });
  });
  document.getElementById('linkedin-profile-link')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    window.posthog?.capture('linkedin_profile_clicked', { source: 'about' });
  });
</script>
